column5: Any updates on Red Cedar Lake water levels? Oh yeah, and fishing reports to.  Cheers,  WeePished Lasalle, On.

I hear its very low. I'm going up in a couple of weeks so I'll report when I get back. Actually, wifey is up there visiting her mom and she is supposed to go to the lake on the weekend so I'll get a report from her.
Thistle is reported as 4 feet or more low Gerry.. and came up a bit last week. Can't see Red Cedar being much different. Temagami is still about 2 feet lower than usual FALL let down level.
Any word on the Lake Levels from your wife? We are going up this coming weekend.

OK, finally got a report to give you.....wifey was having too much fun at the lake to call me! Anyway, the water levels have risen a bit but are still quite low. Can't get to some places on the lake and plenty of 'new' hazards. Apparantly, the fishing has been good.
Thats great, I'll be heading up on Saturday for a week. I'll post something when I get back on the conditions and try and put some pics up.  Cheers!
